#Title#
Penn Foster High School
#Content#
WHY US? PROGRAM & COURSES Penn Foster High School Offers Respected and Accredited Diploma Career Services Included Work at your own pace Online Degrees Tuition & Aid Start Dates Discover Penn Foster High School Penn Foster High School is a regionally and nationally accredited online high school that allows students to earn their diploma from home at their own pace. The high school diploma program is designed for traditional students, student athletes, adult learners who did not complete high school, and homeschoolers; individual course options are also offered in a broad range of subjects for those students who need only a few course credits. Homeschool students are able to control their curriculum by choosing career-focused electives in their area of interest. Parents can take on more of a coaching or mentoring role, rather than that of a primary instructor. Although students homeschool, they are not isolated because they are a part of an online community of high school students. All Penn Foster High School students enjoy the flexibility and convenience of independent study, with expert instructors and support staff available via email and phone to answer questions and assist with coursework when needed. Penn Foster High School students could save an average of $250 for prior credits they've earned.1 The school also offers students low monthly tuition payments with 0% interest. Books, study guides, and learning aids are included in Penn Foster High School programs and are available as soon as their enrollment is accepted. Admission Requirements: Students must be at least 14 years old and have completed the 8th grade. Accreditation You'll earn your High School Diploma from Regionally and Nationally Accredited Penn Foster Career School. Penn Foster High School is accredited by the Accrediting Commission of the Distance Education Accrediting Commission (DEAC), which is listed by the U.S. Department of Education as a nationally recognized accrediting agency. Penn Foster High School is regionally accredited by the Commission on Secondary Schools of the Middle States Association of Colleges and Schools. The Accrediting Commission of the Distance Education and Training Council is also a recognized member of the Council for Higher Education Accreditation (CHEA). Penn Foster High School is licensed by the Pennsylvania State Board of Private Licensed Schools. Penn Foster is a wonderful school. They help you make your dreams come true and care about your future. Thanks for making my dreams come true. — J. Augustus, Penn Foster Graduate If you're thinking about your future and want to get the right education, Penn Foster is the best choice you could ever make. Don't hesitate. — D. Joseph, Penn Foster Graduate Tuition, Financial Aid & Start Dates Since every student is different, there isn't a "one size fits all" for school information. Start dates and tuition often vary between selected programs, and financial aid opportunities are unique to each student's circumstances. Complete the form to the right to get the most up-to-date and accurate information based on your selected program and circumstances. Still have questions? Complete this form to request more info and get your answers and advice. Find Your Program: High School Diploma High School Diploma: Concentration in Building Technology - Carpentry High School Diploma: Concentration in Building Technology - Electrical High School Diploma: Concentration in Building Technology - Plumbing High School Diploma: Concentration in Health Care High School Diploma: Concentration in Information Technology Penn Foster High School with Early College Courses Get your customized answers Call 1-877-619-2902 to speak with an enrollment counselor or simply complete the form below to get program details, tuition, start dates, financial aid, and how to choose the right program for you. When do you plan on starting? --- Select One --- Immediately 1-3 months 4-6 months 6 or more months Unknown On average, 